The Executive Director of Tanzania Private Sector Foundation (TPSF), Francis Nanai has resigned from his position to pursue other personal interests. A statement released by the TPSF Chairperson, Angelina Mabula on February 10, 2022 in Dar es Salaam stated that Mr Nanai resigned from the position effective from February 8, 2022. Following the resignation of Mr Nanai, the TPSF appointed Raphael Laizer as their new Acting Executive Director. “Once again, the Board of Directors would like to thank Mr Francis Nanai for his devotion and commitment towards promoting effective engagement of the private sector in driving the business and development agenda of Tanzania. “The Board would like to reassure all its members, government and all stakeholders of a smooth transition period that will not affect the delivery of the foundation’s mandate,” the statement added.